data.content:
Serious Illness
Serious illness is a health condition that caused the second brother's death.

Eldest Brother
The eldest brother is one of the narrator's older twin brothers who sleeps on the left side of the shared bed.<SEP>The eldest brother is a person who is an older brother of the narrator, shared a childhood bed, and was killed by the narrator.

Death
Death is a concept representing the end of life, occurring when the second brother died.

Narrator
The narrator is a first-person speaker who shares a bed with their older brothers.<SEP>The narrator is a person who shares a sibling relationship with two older brothers and slept in the same bed with them during childhood.

Bed
The bed is a piece of furniture where the narrator and both brothers slept together.<SEP>The bed is an artifact that served as a shared sleeping space for the narrator and both older brothers during childhood.

Second Brother
The second brother is one of the narrator's older twin brothers who sleeps on the right side of the shared bed but later died of a serious illness.<SEP>The second brother is a person who is an older brother of the narrator, shared a childhood bed, and died of illness.

Illness
Illness is a concept representing the cause of death for the second brother.
